{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0246c45d-1905-4f71-88ee-44e7f81d15b5","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_pI8K5ibQoWBO77NIMUnXWc","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"41a57e1c-8e8b-463c-beb9-3af528bf5ca5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the necessary environment variables and pod spec changes.\n\nFor .NET crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` — full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory). Values: 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for the dump file\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` — optional, enables diagnostics for createdump itself\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` — path to the createdump tool since it's at a non-standard location\n\nFor NativeAOT in .NET 8+, crash dump support via createdump is available. I need to set these environment variables and ensure the dump directory exists and is writable through an emptyDir volume in Kubernetes, then show the pod spec changes.","outputTokens":373,"requestId":"C96F:35A1EF:1DD4A5F:2119EB5:6A052982"},"id":"43df6a53-4edd-4702-a317-d3b986a1047a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:46:53.334Z","parentId":"d597e721-1b44-4a97-bfb0-c540cb180991"}
